               this paper use the random forest model through the data from 1903
               Chinese county-level cities in 2010, 2012 and 2015, and establish
               a CO2 forecasting platform based on the effects of urban
               governance elements. The results are as follows: (1) The
               municipal utility facilities element, the economic development \&
               industrial structure element, and the city size \&structure and
               road traffic facilities elements are crucial for residential,
               industrial and transportation CO2 emissions, respectively; (2)
               Governance elements have nonlinear relationship with CO2
