  abstract  = "Climate change will impact electricity markets through both
               electricity demand and supply. This paper reviews the research on
               this topic. Whereas there is much that remains unknown or
               uncertain, research over the last few years has significantly
               advanced our knowledge. In general, higher temperatures are
               expected to raise electricity demand for cooling, decrease demand
               for heating, and to reduce electricity production from thermal
               power plants. The effect of climate change on the supply of
               electricity from non-thermal sources shows great geographical
               variability due to differences in expected changes to temperature
               and precipitation. Whereas the research frontier has advanced
               significantly in the last few years, there still remains a
